Ukuqala Clinical Portal
The Ukuqala Clinical Portal is a human-centric healthcare management system designed to streamline patient record keeping and clinical data tracking. Originally conceived as part of an AI-powered assistive platform, this portal provides practitioners with a clean, professional interface to manage patient demographics, vitals history, and clinical logs securely.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: React (Vite), Axios, React Router.

Backend: Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL.

Documentation: LaTeX (Dissertation) and APA formatting.

🚀 Getting Started
To get the full system running on a fresh machine, follow these steps:

1. Prerequisites
Node.js (v18 or higher)

PostgreSQL (running locally or via Docker)

2. Backend Setup
Navigate to the backend/ directory.

Install dependencies: npm install

Configure your .env file (refer to .env.example).

Initialize the database: npm run migrate (if applicable).

Start the server: npm start

3. Frontend Setup
Navigate to the frontend/ directory.

Install dependencies: npm install

Create a .env file and set VITE_API_URL to your backend address.

Start the application: npm run dev

📁 Project Architecture
This project follows a strict Separation of Concerns to ensure maintainability and scalability:

API Layer: Centralized logic in src/api/ handles all communication with the backend.

State Management: AuthContext manages secure tokens and user sessions.

Modular UI: Reusable components ensure a consistent design system across the dashboard and patient views.

🧪 Testing the Implementation
Evaluators can verify the following end-to-end features:

Authentication: Secure login and logout flow.

Patient Management: Create, read, update, and delete (CRUD) operations on patient profiles.

Clinical Vitals: Record and track patient health metrics over time.

Error Handling: The system includes guardrails to gracefully handle API disconnects or invalid data.

